Nighal 2: I don't know what inspired me to build the contraption in my
	quarters. It seemed to be the right way to examine the stone. Maybe
	the stone itself instructed me, or maybe the Well of Life inspired
	me. I still cannot let myself hope for rescue from the madness that
	grows ever thicker around me. The shadows appear to me constantly,
	the voices grow ever-dissonant. What hope have I for salvation now?

